[Mumps is a viral illness transmitted by the respiratory route, making dissemination possible in gatherings of people. The report does not specify the vaccination coverage of these citizens of the Marshall Islands who have developed the disease, which could be another factor contributing to this outbreak, apart from the possibility of lower effectiveness of the vaccine. It is necessary to investigate further in order to establish with certainty this behavior of the disease. - Mod.JG

See ProMED-mail Mumps - USA (21) 20161008.4545923 for reports of cases in other states in the United States -- Oklahoma and Washington -- and a discussion of the particular problem of providing protection to the Marshallese in Arkansas against vaccine-preventable diseases.

A map showing the location of Arkansas in the United States can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4723331,208 - Mod. LK]

